The paper deals with graph theory and specifically with the concept of interval edge colorings of bipartite graphs. This falls under the category of Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also discusses the maximum degree of bipartite graphs and their interval colorability, which are topics in Graph Theory (cs.GT). The proofs and methods used in the paper involve algorithms and computational techniques, which are relevant to the sub-categories of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) and Computational Geometry (cs.CG). Finally, the paper also mentions the use of computer-aided methods to study interval colorability, which falls under the sub-category of Numerical Analysis (cs.NA).
